      • getImmutable

        public BlockPos getImmutable()
        Returns a version of this BlockPos that is guaranteed to be Immutable. In most cases this will return 'this', but if 'this' is an instance of MutableBlockPos it will return a new instance of BlockPos with the same values. When storing a parameter given to you for an extended period of time, make sure you use this in case the value is changed internally.
        Returns:
        An immutable BlockPos.
